text: Franklin County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. As of the 2020 census, 2,889 people lived there. The county seat is Franklin. The county was founded in 1867 and named after Benjamin Franklin, American statesman. == Communities == * Bloomington * Campbell * Franklin (county seat) * Hildreth * Naponee * Riverton * Upland == References == == Other websites == * Official website Category:1867 establishments in Nebraska Category:Nebraska counties
